@startuml
title User Registration & Authentication

actor User as U
participant "Next.js Frontend" as FE
participant "C# API Controller" as Controller
participant "Auth Handler" as Handler
participant "JWT Service" as JWT
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Email Service" as Email


U -> FE: 1. Enter email/password
FE -> Controller: 2. POST /api/auth/signup
Controller -> Handler: 3. RegisterCommand(email, password)
Handler -> Handler: 4. Hash password (bcrypt)
Handler -> DB: 5. INSERT INTO users
DB --> Handler: 6. User created
Handler -> JWT: 7. Generate verification token
Handler -> Email: 8. Send verification link
Handler --> Controller: 9. Return success
Controller --> FE: 10. 201 Created
FE --> U: 11. "Check your email"


U -> FE: 12. Enter credentials
FE -> Controller: 13. POST /api/auth/login
Controller -> Handler: 14. LoginCommand(email, password)
Handler -> DB: 15. SELECT user WHERE email=?
DB --> Handler: 16. Return user + password_hash
Handler -> Handler: 17. Verify password
Handler -> JWT: 18. Generate tokens
Handler --> Controller: 19. Return tokens
Controller --> FE: 20. 200 OK
FE -> FE: 21. Store tokens
FE --> U: 22. Redirect to dashboard

@enduml